Use `return` to send a value back to the caller.

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    double |value Int| -> Int:
        return value * 2
    ;
]

A function can return more than one success value:

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    pair || -> String, Int:
        return "Ana", 2
    ;

    name, count = pair()
]

The number of receiving names must match the number of returned success values.

Functions that can fail add one final error return marked with `!`. The Errors
page explains how to propagate or recover from that path.
